01:33:17,174 --> 01:33:21,386
So, what do you think this says about the economics discipline?

1459
01:33:21,554 --> 01:33:25,515
Well, l mean, it has no relevance to anything, really.

1460
01:33:25,683 --> 01:33:29,603
And, indeed, I think it's a part of the--

1461
01:33:29,770 --> 01:33:33,690
It's an important part of the problem.

1462
01:33:49,123 --> 01:33:51,625
The rising power of the U.S. financial sector -

1463
01:33:51,792 --> 01:33:54,544
- was part of a wider change in America.

1464
01:33:54,920 --> 01:33:59,549
Since the 1 980s, the United States has become a more unequal society -

1465
01:34:00,092 --> 01:34:03,511
- and its economic dominance has declined.

1466
01:34:03,804 --> 01:34:08,266
Companies like General Motors, Chrysler and U.S. Steel -

1467
01:34:08,434 --> 01:34:11,019
